So, beginning with the breath and then whatever draws the attention within the field of awareness.

224
00:48:42,782 --> 00:48:55,119
So, starting with the breath and then whatever draws your attention in the field of consciousness.

225
00:48:56,213 --> 00:49:25,764
Whatever draws that attention is to be observed, to be felt, to be experienced Lo que llame atención es lo que debes observar, sentir, experimentar Beginning with the breath, rising, falling

226
00:49:27,094 --> 00:49:33,543
Comenzando con la respiración, subiendo, bajando.

227
00:52:33,023 --> 00:53:00,347
becoming more aware of how we are reacting to what we are experiencing how when something is pleasant we're drawn towards it we want to maintain it we want to develop it

228
00:53:01,137 --> 00:53:13,992
¿Cómo si algo nos resulta excitante, queremos mantenerlo, queremos desarrollarlo, nos atrae?

229
00:53:15,755 --> 00:53:23,364
When something is unpleasant, we don't want to feel it, we want to think of something else, we want to push it away.

230
00:53:23,384 --> 00:53:30,773
¿Cómo si algo no nos resulta placentero, no queremos sentirlo,

231
00:53:32,137 --> 00:53:39,625
we want to reject it, we want to eliminate it.

232
00:53:39,644 --> 00:54:01,907
So this sort of desire, which is always manipulating the world in order to make us feel happy and comfortable,

233
00:54:03,894 --> 00:54:06,398
This is the cause of our attachments.

234
00:54:09,039 --> 00:54:20,211
The Buddha says this is the direct cause for our sufferings and unsatisfactoriness.

235
00:54:25,396 --> 00:54:32,164
Is that true for you?

236
00:54:33,139 --> 00:54:35,286
Is this true for you?

237
00:57:05,554 --> 00:57:34,110
becoming more aware of how everything we're experiencing is arising and passing away everything appears only to vanish

238
00:57:35,068 --> 00:57:40,856
Nothing ever repeats itself.

239
00:57:42,539 --> 00:57:45,244
Every breath is similar but not the same.

240
00:57:53,315 --> 00:58:01,347
Can you see anything that you can rely upon?

241
01:00:36,204 --> 01:01:03,715
becoming more aware of how everything I'm experiencing is an object the observer is seeing something

242
01:01:04,387 --> 01:01:32,536
The observer sees a thought or an image The feeler can feel sensations and emotions The experiencer experiences feelings, emotions

243
01:01:33,715 --> 01:01:58,137
and thoughts you can make this distance more obvious to yourself for instance if there is discomfort in the knees

244
01:02:00,007 --> 01:02:09,878
For example, if there is discomfort in the knee, you can say, there, there is discomfort, down there.

245
01:02:13,443 --> 01:02:29,422
So the observer, the feeler is up in the head and the feeling is down in the knee.

246
01:02:30,398 --> 01:02:34,364
¿Y la sensación está abajo en la rodilla?

247
01:02:35,365 --> 01:02:36,507
Same with an emotion.

248
01:02:36,728 --> 01:02:38,411
You can feel it in the body.

249
01:02:39,632 --> 01:02:41,536
Lo mismo con cualquier emoción.

250
01:02:42,516 --> 01:02:44,701
Lo puedes sentir en el cuerpo.

251
01:02:45,081 --> 01:02:46,063
Es un objeto.

252
01:02:47,985 --> 01:02:50,309
Even images you can see in front of you.

253
01:02:51,492 --> 01:02:54,536
Incluso las imágenes las puedes ver en frente de ti.

254
01:02:55,838 --> 01:02:57,942
And thoughts you can be aware of.

255
01:02:59,525 --> 01:03:06,114
y los pensamientos puedes ser consciente de ellos.

256
01:03:06,134 --> 01:03:11,280
So there's a distinction between the observer and the observed.

257
01:03:13,043 --> 01:03:23,358
Así es que hay una distinción entre el que observa y lo observado.

258
01:03:24,259 --> 01:03:26,342
The feeler and the felt.

259
01:03:29,242 --> 01:03:47,327
el que siente y lo sentido and the experiencer and what is being experienced y el experimentador y lo que está siendo experimentado Can the perceiver be the perceived?

260
01:03:49,130 --> 01:03:54,338
Puede el que percibe ser lo percibido

261
01:06:15,949 --> 01:06:23,657
becoming more aware of how everything we're experiencing is arising of its own accord.

262
01:06:26,059 --> 01:06:38,429
Tomando más consciencia de cómo todo lo que surge, lo que va surgiendo, lo va haciendo por sí mismo.

263
01:06:43,893 --> 01:06:45,315
The body offers us

264
01:06:45,547 --> 01:06:48,331
sensations, whether we want it to or not.

265
01:06:49,634 --> 01:06:57,025
El cuerpo nos ofrece sensaciones, tanto si queremos como si no.

266
01:06:57,985 --> 01:06:59,489
Pleasant and unpleasant.

267
01:07:01,090 --> 01:07:04,536
Placenteras y no placenteras.

268
01:07:06,298 --> 01:07:12,568
The heart offers us emotions, pleasant and unpleasant, whether we want it to or not.

269
01:07:13,577 --> 01:07:39,150
The mind is forever thinking and imagining whether we want it to or not.

270
01:07:40,090 --> 01:07:43,315
In this

271
01:07:43,530 --> 01:07:49,298
Vipassana position everything is happening of its own accord.

272
01:07:51,202 --> 01:08:02,237
En toda esta posición de vipassana todo está pasando por sí mismo.

273
01:08:02,257 --> 01:08:03,358
How can they be me?

274
01:08:03,378 --> 01:08:09,706
¿Cómo pueden ellas ser yo?

275
01:10:34,542 --> 01:11:01,409
putting aside all instruction have confidence that this intuitive awareness can understand things directly

276
01:11:02,791 --> 01:11:32,645
Remember that childlike way of looking at things Just observing, feeling, experiencing

277
01:11:32,778 --> 01:11:47,363
sintiendo, experimentando, lo que llame la atención en el campo de la consciencia.

278
01:11:48,265 --> 01:11:55,797
No cambies nada, no hagas nada,

279
01:14:36,579 --> 01:14:40,764
When we come to the end of a sitting, it's good to reflect for a moment.

280
01:14:43,087 --> 01:15:06,452
How diligent were we at bringing ourselves back to the present moment?

281
01:15:17,619 --> 01:15:24,707
If I thought I was diligent, I will congratulate myself.

282
01:15:25,167 --> 01:15:38,101
If I thought I could have been more skillful, I will encourage myself.

283
01:15:42,527 --> 01:15:46,310
No need for self-criticism.

284
01:15:47,742 --> 01:16:16,247
How did we deal with the various physical and mental states that arose?

285
01:16:17,931 --> 01:16:25,902
¿Cómo tratamos con los diversos estados físicos y mentales que surgieron?

286
01:16:27,484 --> 01:16:32,069
Were we experiencing a lot of dullness and lethargy?

287
01:16:33,311 --> 01:16:40,100
¿Estuvimos experimentando mucho abotargamiento y letargia?

288
01:16:41,962 --> 01:16:43,545
Or perhaps agitation?

289
01:16:45,067 --> 01:16:47,229
¿Quizás agitación?

290
01:16:47,800 --> 01:16:50,347
or perhaps an obsessive thinking?

291
01:16:51,371 --> 01:16:59,194
How did we deal with it?

292
01:17:19,576 --> 01:17:24,904
If I thought I was skillful, I will congratulate myself.

293
01:17:26,266 --> 01:17:36,823
If I thought I could have been more skillful, I will encourage myself.

294
01:17:39,247 --> 01:17:46,578
No need for self-criticism.

295
01:17:47,386 --> 01:17:50,130
No hay necesidad para la autocrítica.

296
01:18:09,618 --> 01:18:15,266
Which of those three characteristics of existence was most obvious to us?

297
01:18:16,563 --> 01:18:23,949
¿Cuál de esas tres características de la existencia fueron más obvias para nosotros?

298
01:18:26,011 --> 01:18:33,059
The process of desiring which causes suffering and unsatisfactoriness.

299
01:18:34,180 --> 01:18:41,327
El proceso del deseo que produce sufrimiento e insatisfacción.

300
01:18:42,307 --> 01:18:44,409
How everything is impermanent.

301
01:18:46,600 --> 01:18:48,301
Cómo todo es impermanente.

302
01:18:49,604 --> 01:18:56,192
And how everything is an object, not always under our direct control.

303
01:18:57,613 --> 01:19:03,501
Y cómo todo es un objeto, no siempre bajo nuestro control directo.

304
01:19:05,002 --> 01:19:06,545
Not me, not mine.

305
01:19:08,908 --> 01:19:10,869
No yo, no mío.

306
01:19:24,434 --> 01:19:26,055
And it's good to make a resolution.

307
01:19:26,115 --> 01:19:45,378
Next time I feel sleepy and tired, I will open my eyes immediately.

308
01:20:06,773 --> 01:20:11,921
And don't jump out of the sitting, open the eyes gently, let the light in.

309
01:20:15,627 --> 01:20:34,536
Very good.

310
01:20:35,190 --> 01:20:36,426
Muy bien.

311
01:20:36,447 --> 01:20:37,539
Muy bien.

